sentence: Looking at units outstanding versus one week prior within the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel, the biggest outflow was seen in the SPDR S&P Homebuilders ETF ( XHB ), where 4,150,000 units were destroyed, or a 7.9% decrease week over week.
Among the largest underlying components of XHB, in morning trading today Lowes Companies ( LOW ) is off about 0.9%, and Home Depot ( HD ) is lower by about 0.2%.

And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest outflow was the Daily Developed Markets Bull 3x Shares ( DZK ), which lost 299,999 of its units, representing a 28.6% decline in outstanding units compared to the week prior.
Among the largest underlying components of DZK, in morning trading today Ishares MSCI Eafe Index ( EFA ) is off about 0.4%.
